en_3714929_0	COLOMBO (News 1st) – The current demand of over 100,000 metric tonnes for the local market cannot be met by the existing level of production.
en_3714929_1	Chairman of the Coconut Cultivation Board, Kapila Yakandawala said that steps have been taken to increase the local production of coconut oil by 50%.
en_3714929_2	Thus, reducing the reliance on imported coconut oil.
en_3714929_3	Yakandawala raised concerns of quality and hygiene issues in the imported oil.
